data.name: childbotcommands.Text
data.value: Welcome to your control panel! --- All these commands below are accessible to masters only. #cpanel - displays available commands for masters. -- #online - To change bot status to ONLINE. -- #away - To change bot status to AWAY. -- #busy - To change bot status to BUSY. -- h/help message - to change user help message that is shown when a user sends "HELP". You can use these tags in your help message: %to% = UserID to whom bot is sending the commands, %user% = the bot user, %msg% = current message that is sent/received to/from the user, %masters% = list of bot masters, %L% = new line, %from% = the sender's ID(same to %to%). -- hc/category/user help - To change user help for each category. Ex: hc/protection/To optimize your account use op#id#password...... -- st/status message - to change bot status message Ex: st/Send HELP to get start. -- addm/masterID - to add a new master Ex: addm/ali -- delm/masterID - to delete a master Ex: delm/ali -- addu/userID - to add a user in bot addlist Ex: addu/nissuna -- delu/userID - to delete a user from bot addlist Ex: delu/nissuna -- chat/userID/message - to chat with a user in bot addlist Ex: chat/ali/hi Ali, how is my new bot? -- change/oldCommand/newCommand - to change your bot commands. "oldCommand" is the current command and "newCommand" is the new command you want to apply. EXAMPLE: If you want to change "ent#id#password#roomname" to "join#id#password#roomname" , you will say "change/ent/join' . here "oldCommand" = "ent" and "newCommand" = "join" . NB: once you change a command, old command will no longer work and users should use the new command. So make sure you change the user help message so that they don't use the old command. -- #users - to display online users of the bot. -- #reset - to restart your bot and reset eveything you set to default. Protected accounts, joint roombots, antidc protected accounts and forwarded accounts will not be touched. #logout - to logout this bot(it will disconnect the bot). --- If you find any error in this server, please inform us to fix. >Do you have suggestions/advices? Please help us by giving suggestions and advices our team on how we can improve this server. - email: team@nizzc.com contact form: https://nizzc.com/contact website: https://nizzc.com
